Myelodysplastic syndrome and autoimmune disorders: two sides of the same coin?
We note that systemic inflammatory and autoimmune diseases are often steroid-dependent;  however, studies have also evaluated the roles of other immunomodulating therapies. In this Viewpoint, we critically appraise and review the literature on the epidemiology, pathophysiology, and management of systemic inflammatory and autoimmune diseases that are associated with myelodysplastic syndromes and related diseases.
